{
  "texts": [
    "Statistically significant heterogeneity was observed between subgroups (P = 3.50 × 10 -34), where radiologists with a higher than median treatment effect had a significantly higher treatment effect of 0.472 (95% CI: 0.403 to 0.541) than those with a treatment effect lower than or equal to the median of -0.357 (95% CI: -0.429 to 0.284).",
    "A two-sided, unpaired t-test between the two subgroups of treatment effects was conducted.",
    "Testing for all pathologies aggregated did not constitute multiple hypothesis testing.",
    "The error bars show 95% CIs.",
    "b, Treatment effects on all pathologies aggregated of subgroups of radiologists based on combined characteristics of years of experience, subspecialty in thoracic radiology and experience with AI tools."
  ]
}